Writing Scripts Descended from Egyptian Hieroglyphs

☰


Click the triangles next to the writing script names on the leftmost column to reveal or hide its children scripts.
When expanded, the names of writing scripts are indented in a phylogenetic manner
to show a hierarchical relationship regarding ancestry.

The Expand all and Collapse all buttons reveal and hide the whole phylogenetic tree respectively.

Hover over a letter to see its full name. Click on it for more information.

For more information on each writing script, click its name (when available).

Don't forget to check the side navigation bar for more information regarding this project.

Enjoy learning!

Logography

Egyptian Hieroglyph Gardiner's Sign No. F1

𓃾

Head of Ox

Ideogram for: kꜣ “cattle”
Reconstructed Old Egyptian pronunciation: /kaʀ/
Reconstructed Middle Egyptian pronunciation: /kaʀ/
Reconstructed Late Egyptian pronunciation: /kaʔ/
Modern Egyptological pronunciation: /kɑ/
Conventional Anglicisation: ka
